{"info": {"author": "Nicolas Limage", "author_email": "github@xephon.org", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Environment :: Console", "Intended Audience :: System Administrators", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: Unix", "Programming Language :: Python", "Topic :: Utilities"], "description": "# micron\n\nMinimal replacement for cron in containers\n\n`micron` is made to easily create scheduled-tasks containers,\nwith the following limits:\n\n- 1 task per container\n- 1 schedule per task (cron-compatible)\n- one execution at a time\n  (if the first execution is not finished in time\n  for the next schedule, execution is skipped)\n\n## Installation\n\n```\npip install micron\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```\nusage: micron [-h] [-x] [-q] schedule program [program ...]\n\npositional arguments:\n  schedule             a cron-like schedule\n  program              the command line to run\n\noptional arguments:\n  -h, --help           show this help message and exit\n  -x, --exit-on-error  exit if the program return-code is non-zero\n  -q, --quiet          do not log micron actions\n```\n\nExample\n\n```\nmicron '0 0 * * *' -- find /var/log -name '*.log' -mtime +30 -delete\n```\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/nlm/micron", "keywords": "crontab container", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "micron", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/micron/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/micron/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/nlm/micron"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/micron/1.0.post1/", "requires_dist": ["crontab"], "requires_python": ">=3.6", "summary": "minimal cron alternative for containers", "version": "1.0.post1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>micron</h1>\n<p>Minimal replacement for cron in containers</p>\n<p><code>micron</code> is made to easily create scheduled-tasks containers,\nwith the following limits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 task per container</li>\n<li>1 schedule per task (cron-compatible)</li>\n<li>one execution at a time\n(if the first execution is not finished in time\nfor the next schedule, execution is skipped)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<pre><code>pip install micron\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre><code>usage: micron [-h] [-x] [-q] schedule program [program ...]\n\npositional arguments:\n  schedule             a cron-like schedule\n  program              the command line to run\n\noptional arguments:\n  -h, --help           show this help message and exit\n  -x, --exit-on-error  exit if the program return-code is non-zero\n  -q, --quiet          do not log micron actions\n</code></pre>\n<p>Example</p>\n<pre><code>micron '0 0 * * *' -- find /var/log -name '*.log' -mtime +30 -delete\n</code></pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6761530, "releases": {"1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "bf4fccd4a8aa7a9d866f8e5377271bd5", "sha256": "61b132ba2c90cacbbf0fb69cfb9a8eabd3da6707726193700140ecc316b7eadb"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "micron-1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "bf4fccd4a8aa7a9d866f8e5377271bd5", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 2970, "upload_time": "2020-03-05T13:01:05", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-05T13:01:05.486678Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/80/32/3194f08c293773b21af34641fb7ffc3c44535f1164b825b9fda25fe8dcb4/micron-1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "f8039d6b8abdaeebb108d5b3d37aec7e", "sha256": "c5a1ea169d6fe53814d53baf27f859a6e28c650817a609bc28b607bba2e5e21f"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "micron-1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "f8039d6b8abdaeebb108d5b3d37aec7e", "pac